%section.footnotes
  = footnote do
    This -ū- is the reflex of an historical Semitic *ā stative marker, seen in some other Semitic languages but largely lost in Alashian.

  = footnote do
    The semantic progression from 'cause to ask' to 'lend' is not entirely clear. There was presumably an intermediate stage something along the lines of “offer”.

  = footnote do
    The semantic connection between between the <i>katab</i> meaning “gather” and the <i>'aktēb</i> meaning “insert” is not clear, yet this pair is seen in several Semitic languages. The semantic divergence is either very old, or else these two forms represent entirely unrelated roots that happened to merge phonetically in Semitic.
